Text.Value: The Absolute? That's one god I don't know.
The Absolute? I've seen no mention of Her in my studies.
Another god? I swear, Toril has more deities than there are stars in the sky.
The Absolute? Can't say I know your god.
We're runnin' out of time. They're gonna murder me!

EditorData.logicalname: You haven't promised to free me!

Text.Value: I just saved your life. Show some gratitude.
Don't believe you. There's something a bit soft about you.
Don't believe you. You ain't got enough scars to be one of her playthings.
They're gonna burn this pretty place for the glory of the Absolute and 'ang ya by yer guts.
Got a whole lab set up. Cooks up potions that fix our lads no matter how much of a beatin' they take.
They'll peel yer face off and nail it to a wall!
You won't regret it, promise.
You've caught my interest. Have any holy literature on you?
I been patient. So hurry it up, yeah?
Goddess.
Suit yerself. Lookin' forward to seein' wot yer innards look like.
Patience. I'll get you out soon.
Wotcher messin' with my cage for?

EditorData.NodeContext: spoken when player tampers with her cage while she's locked up - curious

Text.Value: Nobody sent me.
The Absolute is gold from the sky, She is. The blessin' in the storm an' the storm itself.
Maybe She sent you to help me. An' ya will, if ya wanna save yer skin.
I already met your friend. You here to get me out of here?
Yer a long way from 'ome, ain't ya, underdwarf?
We'll be heroes, blessed by Priestess Gut in the name of the Absolute.
The Absolute is gold from the sky, She is. The blessin' in the storm an' the storm itself.

EditorData.NodeContext: speaking of her god - the Absolute - awe.

Text.Value: Do I look like I'm scared of goblins? I'll smash 'em, like the last lot I ran into.
They can try, but they won't be the first goblins I've killed today.
You gonna open this cage or wot?
Get me outta here, and I'll take you to meet her and the rest of my tribe.
Well, 'urry up. I got all the time in the world. You don't.
Didn't expect to see a drow in here. Did the boss lady send you to rescue me?
You need me - get me outta here, and I'll tell 'em what a good friend you are.

EditorData.NodeContext: heavy emphasis on 'need' - she's convinced she's winning us over

Text.Value: Yes, she sent me. Ready to get out of here?
I'm not saying we should trust a goblin, but she sounds very useful.

EditorData.NodeContext: Half muttered to his companion. Emphasis on 'very'

Text.Value: We got more than ya can handle. And our priestess keeps us fightin' even if someone sticks a few holes in us.
Who's your 'boss lady'?
Priestess Gut is quite the name. Tell me more.
Yer a long way from 'ome, ain't ya, underdwarf?
Get me outta 'ere, an' I'll introduce you to my tribe. You'd like 'em.
Ah, the 'Absolute'. This is the deity you're bowing to?
All right. I'll see what I can do.
Well, if you make it worth my while...
Not a chance. You can rot in that cage.
Any luck openin' this cage?
I'd sooner swig a flask of acid than anything a goblin cooks up.
Leave.
Yeah. Take me back to the tribe, and we'll tell the boss all about this pretty little place so she can burn it to the ground.
Just be patient. I'll break you free soon enough.
Booyahg - the goblin word for magic. Primitive to a fault, but not entirely without merit.
Who is this Absolute?
Ha! Even if you did find my tribe, they'd set the worgs on ya.
Sounds like tall tales to me.
Nice story. Buy it for a copper in a tavern nearby?
I ain't scared of some guard. Stick a dozen arrows in me, and Priestess Gut'd still patch me up.
Deal. I'll get you out of there.
You already told me what I need to know. I'll find the priestess myself.
It's too late to make friends, worgmeat. My tribe's comin'.
Ain't sure why ya protected me. Don't care, neither.
The lady that sent me here's the cruellest drow I ever met. You could learn a thing or two from her.
The power of the Absolute, of course! Priestess Gut will tell you all about it and make sure you have everything you need.
Runnin' out of time, worgmeat. My family'll be 'ere soon. Lemme out.

EditorData.logicalname: You haven't promised to free me!

Text.Value: A goblin healer. We really are desperate, aren't we?
And if the tiefs stick a few arrows in us on the way out of here, don't worry. Priestess Gut'll patch us up.
Actions have consequences, Sazza. Maybe use this time in the cage to reflect.
We're burnin' Her name across the face o' the world, we are.

EditorData.NodeContext: speaking of her god - the Absolute - awe.

Text.Value: Ain't sure why ya killed yer own to protect me. Don't care, neither.
Ain't sure why ya killed that soft-arse to protect me. Don't care, neither.
It's the truth - I swear on your mother's grave.

EditorData.NodeContext: as if swearing a solemn oath

Text.Value: Yes, she sent me. Ready to get out of here?
My tribe can tell you everythin' there is to know. Absolute blessed one of our own - Priestess Gut.

EditorData.NodeContext: Very arrogant - extremely pleased that a goblin has been chosen to be blessed

Text.Value: An all-powerful goddess that can't get you out of a cage?
You're not mates with the tiefs, are you? You need to get back to your own people before you go soft.
Another drow - she's one of my best mates. Thought you might work for her.
Could probably stick yer head back on if someone woz to chop it off. Mighty booyahg.
Bah. A clever goblin's like a trustworthy ghaik: a figment of the imagination.
What could a tribe of goblins possibly offer me?
Then hurry up an' do it. My tribe ain't as friendly as I am.
Well, I'd certainly like to meet her.
We're burnin' Her name across the face o' the world, we are.
Leave.
Aw, c'mon. We could be mates.
The Absolute? If that's your god, I don't know them.
In all my studies, I've seen no reference to a god called the Absolute.
Another god? I swear, Toril has more deities than there are stars in the sky.
Who is this Absolute you're so fond of? Your god?
'Course I do. We all do.
Get me out of 'ere and I'll tell you where to find 'er. Deal?

EditorData.NodeContext: Thinks she's offering a GREAT deal

Text.Value: Yeah, 'ow many were there? Four?
Oh, look - one of ya found the stones to talk to me rather than cryin' an' moanin' about yer dead mates.
They're gonna burn this pretty place for the glory of the Absolute and 'ang ya by yer guts.
Goblins belong in cages. You won't be getting my help.
I wonder how she feels about trepanning.
Didn't expect to see a drow in here. Did the boss lady send you to rescue me?
No point turnin' on yer own if yer just gonna give 'em a little tap.

Synopsis: Character is caged for this entire dialogue If the player saves the goblin captive from being killed, the goblin will try to convince the player to free them and then meet the player later in the goblin camp.
